1 Create Euclidean Distance Matrix for depth

All Survey Samples

depth<-read.table(file="../processed_data/depth.txt", header=T, row.names=1,sep='\t')

# Create depth distance matrix and export
(depth.dist = dist(depth, method = "euclidean", diag=TRUE, upper=FALSE))    
depth.matrix <- matrix(depth.dist)
    #length(depth.matrix)
    #write.table(depth.matrix, file = '../processed_data/depth.matrix.txt')


LHSS

depth_LHSS<-read.table(file="../processed_data/depth_LHSS.txt", header=T, row.names=1,sep='\t')

# Create depth distance matrix and export
(depth.dist_LHSS = dist(depth_LHSS, method = "euclidean", diag=TRUE, upper=FALSE))  
depth.matrix_LHSS <- matrix(depth.dist_LHSS)
    #length(depth.matrix)
    #write.table(depth.matrix_LHSS, file = '../processed_data/depth.matrix_LHSS.txt')


WHC

depth_WHC<-read.table(file="../processed_data/depth_WHC.txt", header=T, row.names=1,sep='\t')

# Create depth distance matrix and export
(depth.dist_WHC = dist(depth_WHC, method = "euclidean", diag=TRUE, upper=FALSE))    
depth.matrix_WHC <- matrix(depth.dist_WHC)
    #length(depth.matrix)
    #write.table(depth.matrix_WHC, file = '../processed_data/depth.matrix_WHC.txt')


2 Generate Distance Matrices for OTU Tables

All Survey Samples

# Read in the OTU table for all of the data and transpose with R    
    bact.97 = read.csv('../processed_data/AL_Survey_bac_97_nosing.csv', header=T, row.names=1)

# Create presence absence matrix
bact.97.pres.abs = decostand(x=bact.97, method="pa")

# Create distance matrix for beta diversity metrices
bact.97.dist = beta.pair(bact.97.pres.abs, index.family="sor")

    (bact.97.dist.sor.matrix <- matrix(bact.97.dist$beta.sor))
    length(bact.97.dist.sor.matrix)
    # write.table(bact.97.dist.sor.matrix, file = '../processed_data/survey.97.org.dist.sor.matrix.txt')
    
    (bact.97.dist.sim.matrix <- matrix(bact.97.dist$beta.sim))
    length(bact.97.dist.sim.matrix)
    # write.table(bact.97.dist.sim.matrix, file = '../processed_data/survey.97.org.dist.sim.matrix.txt')
    
    (bact.97.dist.sne.matrix <- matrix(bact.97.dist$beta.sne))
    length(bact.97.dist.sne.matrix)
    # write.table(bact.97.dist.sne.matrix, file = '../processed_data/survey.97.org.dist.sne.matrix.txt')

3 Run MRM Model

All Survey Samples

bact.97.dist.sor.mrm <- MRM(bact.97.dist$beta.sor ~ depth.matrix, nperm=1000)
bact.97.dist.sim.mrm <- MRM(bact.97.dist$beta.sim ~ depth.matrix, nperm=1000)
bact.97.dist.sne.mrm <- MRM(bact.97.dist$beta.sne ~ depth.matrix, nperm=1000)

sor.b.m <- c(bact.97.dist.sor.mrm$coef[1,1], bact.97.dist.sor.mrm$coef[2,1])
sim.b.m <- c(bact.97.dist.sim.mrm$coef[1,1], bact.97.dist.sim.mrm$coef[2,1])
sne.b.m <- c(bact.97.dist.sne.mrm$coef[1,1], bact.97.dist.sne.mrm$coef[2,1])


LHSS

survey.LHSS.dist.sor.mrm <- MRM(survey.LHSS.dist$beta.sor ~ depth.matrix_LHSS, nperm=1000)
survey.LHSS.dist.sim.mrm <- MRM(survey.LHSS.dist$beta.sim ~ depth.matrix_LHSS, nperm=1000)
survey.LHSS.dist.sne.mrm <- MRM(survey.LHSS.dist$beta.sne ~ depth.matrix_LHSS, nperm=1000)

survey.LHSS.sor.b.m <- c(survey.LHSS.dist.sor.mrm$coef[1,1], survey.LHSS.dist.sor.mrm$coef[2,1])
survey.LHSS.sim.b.m <- c(survey.LHSS.dist.sim.mrm$coef[1,1], survey.LHSS.dist.sim.mrm$coef[2,1])
survey.LHSS.sne.b.m <- c(survey.LHSS.dist.sne.mrm$coef[1,1], survey.LHSS.dist.sne.mrm$coef[2,1])


WHC

survey.WHC.dist.sor.mrm <- MRM(survey.WHC.dist$beta.sor ~ depth.matrix_WHC, nperm=1000)
survey.WHC.dist.sim.mrm <- MRM(survey.WHC.dist$beta.sim ~ depth.matrix_WHC, nperm=1000)
survey.WHC.dist.sne.mrm <- MRM(survey.WHC.dist$beta.sne ~ depth.matrix_WHC, nperm=1000)

survey.WHC.sor.b.m <- c(survey.WHC.dist.sor.mrm$coef[1,1], survey.WHC.dist.sor.mrm$coef[2,1])
survey.WHC.sim.b.m <- c(survey.WHC.dist.sim.mrm$coef[1,1], survey.WHC.dist.sim.mrm$coef[2,1])
survey.WHC.sne.b.m <- c(survey.WHC.dist.sne.mrm$coef[1,1], survey.WHC.dist.sne.mrm$coef[2,1])


4 Plotting

All Survey Samples

par(mfrow=c(3,1))


matplot(depth.matrix, bact.97.dist.sor.matrix, pch="O", col="black", 
        ylim=c(0,1), cex=1.2, cex.lab=1.2, cex.axis=1.1,
        main="Total dissimilarity (Sørensen)\n R^2 = 0.09, P = 0.001",
        xlab="", ylab="Sørensen Dissimilarity")
    abline(coef = sor.b.m)
    #(r.sq.sor <- (bact.97.dist.sor.mrm)$r.squared)
    #legend("bottom", legend = bquote(paste(R^2 == . ("0.05")),paste(P == . ("0.001"))), text.col="black", bty="n")

matplot(depth.matrix, bact.97.dist.sim.matrix, pch="O", col="black", 
        ylim=c(0,1), cex=1.2, cex.lab=1.2, cex.axis=1.1,
        main="Turnover-resultant dissimilarity\n R^2 = 0.08, P = 0.001",
        xlab="",
        ylab="Simpson Dissimilarity")
    abline(coef = sim.b.m)
    #(r.sq.sor <- (bact.97.dist.sor.mrm)$r.squared)
    #legend("bottom", legend = bquote(paste(R^2 == . ("0.003"))), text.col="black", bty="n")
    
    
matplot(depth.matrix, bact.97.dist.sne.matrix, pch="O", col="black", 
        ylim=c(0,1), cex=1.2, cex.lab=1.2, cex.axis=1.1,
        main="Nestedness-resultant dissimilarity\n R^2 = 0.0003 (not significant, P = 0.77)",
        xlab=expression(paste("Depth (cm)")), 
        ylab="Sørensen - Simpson Dissimilarity")
    abline(coef = sne.b.m)


LHSS
